Delivery Review:
Ordered regular thali/meals and plain milk.
Food Quality : 2.5/5
The gravy/sabji were doused in a lot of oil. You could see a thick layer of red coloured oil over all of them. The vegetables were small in quantity compared to the wet gravy.
The plain milk was hot but had some kind of brown dust (or) substance floating in it (not talking about the cream/malai). It seemed they had used a dirty pan for heating the milk.
The rotis were usual sized phulka and regular white rice; no complaint there.
Food Quantity: 4/5
The meal included around 6 rotis (phulka), bowl of rice, buttermilk, 5 gravy/sabji (mostly wet), sides.
Food Packaging: 3/5
All gravies were packed in thin plastic covers and had oil dripping all over them. Use of aluminium foil covers for rotis and plain milk.

This place is pocket friendly although the food is too spicy. The owner looks at you as if you did any crime but the working staff is good. Food quality doesn't meet the standard and sometimes you might even get upset stomach or a heartburn after consuming their extra spicy food. Rice seems to be of cheap quality, may be they add some soda in it.
If you are ordering any customized dish like Aloo Paratha then make sure to inform them about your spice meter.
Also FYI..... For 100 bucks, you will get unlimited food but eat at your own risk :P
